         <abstract id="aspace_cc52887cd7c6876fd5b862573666da94">Nearly half the papers are made up of the texts of Edward Livingston Wells' sermons and a series of lectures on Genesis. The remainder consists of notes (in French) made while he was a student at the Protestant Theological Seminary in Montauban, France.</abstract>
